products.description:
The Eastern Mediterranean Chermoula from Santa Maria is an oily North African spice blend combining loads of fresh herbs to get a bold and refreshing taste profile. This bright green chermoula spice mix brings a rich, herbal taste thanks to a lot of parsley and coriander leaves, but also a tangy kick from vinegar slight spiciness from chili and garlic. Itâ€™s smooth yet a little grainy, much like an Argentinian chimichurri or an Italian pesto. Serve the chermoula blend with crusty bread, mix it with yoghurt or simply dress grilled meats and vegetables. Spread on grilled cheese sandwiches, use as topping for salads or spice up shrimp cocktails and moules frites. The chermoula paste can also be drizzled over poached eggs, stirred into rice and potato salads or combined with cream for simple pasta sauces.

products.description:
The Eastern Mediterranean Preserved Lemon Paste from Santa Maria provides the sunny taste of pickled lemons in a handy format that helps you save time and space. It packs bright,spirited and tangy lemon flavours with pungent aroma from the peel and more acidic notes from the pulp and juice. All perfectly balanced with a bit of salt. The consistency is smooth and pretty thick yet pourable. Use this convenient take on preserved lemons to flavour sauces and dressings,spread on salmon before grilling or boost the taste of tagines and shakshukas. Infuse marinades for chicken or stir into yoghurt with some garlic and herbs for a lovely dip. You can also mix it with olives and capers to make tapenade or simply add some tang to couscous,pilaf and risotto.

products.description: The Eastern Mediterranean Harissa Sauce from Santa Maria is a North African classic starring in many dishes thanks to its warmth and depth of flavours. This deep red chili sauce provides a spicy and smoky taste including garlic,cumin and coriander,distinctive heat,a hint of sweetness and fresh citrus notes to balance it all. Itâ€™s smooth and creamy with tiny spice grains. Compared to other varieties,this is a thinner harissa sauce rather than a harissa paste. Serve it right away as topping or dipping sauce,swap the ketchup or season shakshukas and other tomato-based dishes. Add to your hummus for a fiery kick or mix with honey and use as glaze. You can also make harissa butter for corn cobs or infuse chocolates and martinis. â€¢ North African chili sauce for chefs â€¢ Warm,spicy and smoky taste â€¢ Hot but not overpowering â€¢ Serve right away as topping sauce or dip â€¢ Shortcut to perfect shakshukas sauce
